      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://dpertin.github.io/authors/dim/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;After receiving a Master of Engineering degree in Systems and Networks from the
University of Nantes in 2012, I started a

&lt;a href=&#34;https://hal.archives-ouvertes.fr/tel-01720038v1&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Ph.D&lt;/a&gt;
 in computer science
about the designing of fault-tolerant, low-cost and high-performance coding
techniques for distributed storage systems. With funding from

&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.rozosystems.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Rozo Systems&lt;/a&gt;
, and under the supervision of
Nicolas Normand and Benoît Parrein, I defended my thesis in 2016.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since then, I have been working on the

&lt;a href=&#34;http://beyondtheclouds.github.io/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Discovery Initiative&lt;/a&gt;
 as a postdoctoral
researcher, at the 
&lt;a href=&#34;http://stack.inria.fr/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;STACK&lt;/a&gt;
 team of Inria and LS2N. My
research deals with distributed application deployment and reconfiguration on
dynamic and massively-distributed infrastructures (e.g. Fog and Edge
computing).&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
